			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2017</a> paper:</span><br><i>A development environment for the Alf language within the MagicDraw UML tool (tool demo)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/EdSeidewitz.html">Ed Seidewitz</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3136014.3136028">10.1145/3136014.3136028</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The paper presents an IDE/development environment (in MagicDraw) for the Alf action language.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It focuses on integrating a textual action language with UML models inside an existing modeling tool.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> Alf is a domain-specific action language for expressing executable behavior in UML models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagL">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> The work is demonstrated in a commercial/industrial-grade modeling tool context (MagicDraw).
</li></ul></li></ul>
